Date: Fri, 29 Jul 2011 14:46:51 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] net/dpa: set CONFIG_FSL_FMAN default value as n

Currently CONFIG_FSL_FMAN is enabled by default, and the
result is CONFIG_FSL_FMAN is always y in all boards. it is not
right(even no harm), so here set CONFIG_FSL_FMAN to n by default.
CONFIG_FSL_FMAN needs to be turned on explicitly in board cfg.

Signed-off-by: Weiwei Wang <weiwei.wang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/dpa/NetCommSw/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/dpa/NetCommSw/Kconfig b/drivers/net/dpa/NetCommSw/Kconfig
index cf84529..ff06db0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/dpa/NetCommSw/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/dpa/NetCommSw/Kconfig
@@ -3,7 +3,7 @@ menu "Frame Manager support"
 menuconfig FSL_FMAN
 	bool "Freescale Frame Manager (datapath) support"
 	# depends on PPC_E500MC
-	default y
+	default n
 	---help---
 	  If unsure, say Y.
 
